.

💻 Programming Languages (most impactful for full-stack)

JavaScript (ES6+) → Core of React, Node.js, Express

Python → Backend logic, scripting, APIs, data tools

SQL → Database queries, schema design

Java → OOP foundation, scalable architecture knowledge

C# → Secondary backend language (useful via Unity & enterprise contexts)

HTML → Structure & accessibility

CSS → Styling & responsive layout

⚙️ Frameworks & Libraries

React → Core front-end framework for UI development

Node.js → Server-side runtime environment

Express → Backend routing, APIs, middleware

Vite → Build tool & dev server (React projects)

Tailwind CSS → Utility-first styling for rapid UI design

EJS → Server-side templating (used in earlier projects)

Unity → Secondary, game-based or simulation development

🧠 Technologies & Tools

PostgreSQL → Primary relational database, production-ready

REST APIs → Core method of client-server communication

AWS → Cloud hosting, scaling, and deployment infrastructure

Passport.js (Auth) → Authentication and user sessions

Cloudinary → Image and file storage integration

Git / GitHub → Version control and collaboration

OOP & Data Structures → Core computer science fundamentals

Railway / Render → Hosting and deployment platforms

Web Scraping → Automation and data collection

🧩 Development Practices

Full-Stack Web Development → End-to-end design and implementation

Authentication & Authorization → Secure login and user management

API Integration → Connecting client & server layers

Responsive UI / UX → Clean design and usability across devices

Scalable Architecture → Handling high traffic and data loads

Database Management & Modeling → Efficient queries, schema design

Version Control Workflow (Git) → Team collaboration best practices